Core work, similar to balancing postures, encourages you to take stock and embody the present moment as a way of creating sustainable strength and stamina. description: Please join me for this 28-minute at-home yoga practice designed to help you feel good and bring you back into a balanced state. As we know, emotional, mental, and/or physical stress can lead to the collection of tension in the mind and body. title: Day 9 - Balance |  BREATH - A 30 Day Yoga Journey
tags: home yoga|home yoga practice|yoga at home|at home yoga|Adriene Mishler|austin yoga instructor|free yoga|free yoga videos|full yoga class|morning yoga|online yoga|yoga practice|yoga with Adrienne|breath|30 days of yoga|30 day yoga journey|30 day yoga challenge|30 day challenge
description: The YWA POP UP Shop is Live! Find custom made designs for BREATH - A 30 Day Yoga Journey designed by independent artists on organic cotton, using renewable energy. http://yogawithadriene.com/shop- - - -We ease in to practice today with a breath technique that can help balance out the brain and body. Alternate Nostril Breathing, also called Nadhi Shodana, is an incredible tool for activating the parasympathetic nervous system which can restore balance - particularly if you are consciously, or subconsciously, living more in fight or flight mode - which is common in such uncertain times. We will introduce the powerful play of opposites in yoga asana as well, considering the ways in which we may join steadiness, or STHIRA, with ease, or SUKHA.I will guide postures today that are there not to discourage you, but to help you play with the concept of how to create a dance for both steadiness and ease, and one that is individual for you. I invite you to use this material to check in, learn, and grow. Remember, it‚Äôs not about being able to stand on one foot. title: Lucid Dreaming - Guided Hypnosis with Binaural Beats
tags: Lights of Venus|guided hypnosis|Lucid Dreaming|OBE|female voice
description: This guided hypnosis is designed to induce lucid dreaming. To Lucid dream is to become conscious within a dream. Once conscious and aware, you can direct events in any way you like. You may for example want to act out some of your fantasies, seek answers to real life problems or gain other meaningful insight through thoughtful interactions. If you would like to give this hypnosis a try, it is best to do so an estimated 30 mins before you would usually fall asleep. For best results, it is recommended not to consume any heavy, processed foods and liquids (including caffeinated beverages) at least 4 hours before going to bed. If possible, no food consumption is preferable. This session uses the commonly known 'Reality Check' technique which helps you become aware of your current reality, whether it'd be in your waking state or inside your dream. Whilst in a dream, you are thus encouraged to become lucid. Our Reality Check will be presented to you in the form of several questions which you will be asked to answer based on your perception and awareness.The Structure Of Our Hypnosis:- Introduction- Awareness Practice (Preparation for the Reality Checks)- Relaxation- Reality Check (Whilst Awake)- Deepening of the Relaxation (Falling Asleep)- 'Lucid Dreaming' Hypnotic Suggestions- Deep Sleep (1 hour)- REM Sleep / Dreaming (1 hour 13 mins)- 'Lucid Dreaming' Induction (Spoken Words Return)- Reality Check (Whilst Dreaming)- REM Sleep / Dreaming (10 mins)- Reality Check (Whilst Dreaming - 2nd attempt)- End of SessionI hope you'll enjoy this session. Best of luck and sweet lucid dreams! :)~Lights of Venus~-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------https://www.facebook.com/lightsofvenus/https://twitter.com/Lights_of_Venushttps://soundcloud.com/lightsofvenus-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------This audio uses binaural beats and an isochronic pulse. (Alpha, Theta and Delta waves) For best results, please wear headphones. Both binaural beats and Isochronic tones are present using the following frequencies:211.44 Hz - ¬≠Neptune Frequency / Intuition / Imagination / The Unconsciousness / Enhances the dream experience1052 Hz - Crown Chakra / Spirit / Liberation / Transcendence----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------¬© 2020. Lights of Venus Entertainment. All rights reserved.----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------#LightsOfVenus #Lucid Dreaming #Guided #Hypnosis

description: This guided hypnosis is designed to induce lucid dreaming. To Lucid dream is to become conscious within a dream. Once conscious and aware, you can direct events in any way you like. You may for example want to act out some of your fantasies, seek answers to real life problems or gain other meaningful insight through thoughtful interactions. If you would like to give this hypnosis a try, it is best to do so an estimated 30 mins before you would usually fall asleep. For best results, it is recommended not to consume any heavy, processed foods and liquids (including caffeinated beverages) at least 4 hours before going to bed. If possible, no food consumption is preferable. This session uses the commonly known 'Reality Check' technique which helps you become aware of your current reality, whether it'd be in your waking state or inside your dream. Whilst in a dream, you are thus encouraged to become lucid. Our Reality Check will be presented to you in the form of several questions which you will be asked to answer based on your perception and awareness.The Structure Of Our Hypnosis:- Introduction- Awareness Practice (Preparation for the Reality Checks)- Relaxation- Reality Check (Whilst Awake)- Deepening of the Relaxation (Falling Asleep)- 'Lucid Dreaming' Hypnotic Suggestions- Deep Sleep (1 hour)- REM Sleep / Dreaming (1 hour 13 mins)- 'Lucid Dreaming' Induction (Spoken Words Return)- Reality Check (Whilst Dreaming)- REM Sleep / Dreaming (10 mins)- Reality Check (Whilst Dreaming - 2nd attempt)- End of SessionI hope you'll enjoy this session.
